#: includes/Core/Blocks.php:150
msgid "Blockish Framework"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/ExtensionList.php:34
msgid "Create reusable global CSS classes and apply them to any Blockish block."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/ExtensionList.php:41
msgid ""
"Exposes Blockish abilities (posts, blocks, CSS classes) to AI tools over "
"the Model Context Protocol for this entire site. Enable only if you trust "
"the AI client connecting to this site ? it can create and edit content and "
"CSS classes."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:32
msgid "Container"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:33
msgid ""
"The primary layout and structure block. Use it to build hero sections, "
"feature grids, card rows, full-width banners, or any section wrapper. "
"Supports both flexbox and CSS grid layouts with full background, border, "
"and shadow styling including hover states. Any HTML semantic tag can be "
"used (div, section, article, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:38
msgid "Icon"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:39
msgid ""
"Displays a single SVG icon with color, size, rotation, and an optional "
"link. Use for decorative accents, feature highlights, or standalone icon "
"links."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:44
msgid "Heading"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:45
msgid ""
"A heading block (H1?H6) with per-device text alignment, typography, color, "
"hover color, and text shadow. Use for page titles, section headings, and "
"card labels when custom styling beyond the core heading is needed."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:50
msgid "Image"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:51
msgid ""
"Displays an image with full visual control including custom dimensions, "
"object-fit, opacity, CSS filters, border, shadow, and hover transition "
"effects. Also supports captions. Use when more styling control than the "
"core image block is needed."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:56
msgid "Button"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:57
msgid ""
"A call-to-action button with a label, URL, optional icon (before or after "
"text), and full hover styling for color, background, border, and shadow. "
"Use for CTAs, download links, or any interactive link that needs custom "
"visual design."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:62
msgid "Video"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:63
msgid ""
"Embeds a video from YouTube, Vimeo, or a self-hosted file. Supports "
"autoplay, loop, lazy load, start/end time, aspect ratio, privacy mode, and "
"a custom poster image with overlay play button. Use for product demos, "
"testimonials, or media-rich sections."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:68
msgid "Google Map"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:69
msgid ""
"Embeds a Google Map for a given location with configurable zoom and height. "
"Use for contact pages, store locators, or any page that needs to display a "
"physical location."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:74
msgid "Icon List"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:75
msgid ""
"A list of icon and text pairs displayed in a column or row layout. Use for "
"feature lists, checklists, service highlights, or any bulleted content that "
"benefits from custom icons instead of plain bullets. Contains "
"icon-list-item child blocks."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:80
msgid "Icon List Item"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:81
msgid ""
"A single icon and text row inside an Icon List block. Each item has its own "
"text, icon, and optional link. Must be placed inside an Icon List block."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:87
msgid "Rating"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:88
msgid ""
"Displays a visual star (or custom icon) rating with a configurable scale "
"and decimal value. Use for product reviews, service ratings, or testimonial "
"sections."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:93
msgid "Counter"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:94
msgid ""
"An animated number that counts up to a target value on scroll. Supports a "
"prefix, suffix, thousand separator, and a title label positioned above or "
"below the number. Use for statistics sections ? e.g. \"500+ clients\", "
"\"99% uptime\", \"$2M raised\"."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:99
msgid "Progress Bar"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:100
msgid ""
"An animated horizontal bar that fills to a given percentage on scroll. "
"Supports a title, an inner text label inside the fill, and custom colors. "
"Use for skills sections, fundraising progress, or any percentage-based "
"visual indicator."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:105
msgid "Social Icons"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:106
msgid ""
"A grid of social media icon links with shape options (circle, square, "
"rounded), official brand colors or custom colors, hover animations, and "
"flexible column layout. Use in headers, footers, author bios, or contact "
"sections. Contains social-icon-item child blocks."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:111
msgid "Social Icon Item"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:112
msgid ""
"A single social network link inside a Social Icons block. Defines the "
"network (facebook, instagram, linkedin, youtube, etc.), its icon, brand "
"color, and URL. Must be placed inside a Social Icons block."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:118
msgid "Accordion"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:119
msgid ""
"A collapsible accordion that can allow one or multiple items open at once. "
"Supports FAQ structured data markup for SEO. Use for FAQs, product specs, "
"or any expandable Q&A content. Contains accordion-item child blocks."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:124
msgid "Accordion Item"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:125
msgid ""
"A single collapsible panel inside an Accordion block. Has a title, a "
"default-open option, and customizable expand/collapse icons. The content "
"area accepts any inner blocks. Must be placed inside an Accordion block."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:131
msgid "Tab"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:132
msgid ""
"A tabbed content container with horizontal or vertical tab navigation, "
"configurable active tab, and optional icons on each tab. Use for product "
"details, service categories, pricing tiers, or any multi-section content "
"that benefits from tab navigation. Contains tab-item child blocks."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:137
msgid "Tab Item"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:138
msgid ""
"A single tab panel inside a Tab block. Has a title, an optional icon, and a "
"default-active option. The content area accepts any inner blocks. Must be "
"placed inside a Tab block."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:144
msgid "Navigation"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:145
msgid "Navigation wrapper pairing a desktop menu with a mobile offcanvas."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:150
msgid "Nav Menu"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:151
msgid "Navigation menu block for headers and footers."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:157
msgid "Nav Menu Item"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:158
msgid "Item for the Nav Menu block."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:164
msgid "Off Canvas"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Config/BlocksList.php:165
msgid "Slide-in offcanvas panel that mirrors a nav menu."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/WriteBlog/Config.php:14
msgid "Write Blog Post"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/WriteBlog/Config.php:15
msgid ""
"Writes or edits a blog post (omit post_id to create, provide it to edit; "
"defaults to post type \"post\") using WordPress CORE blocks only ? never "
"blockish custom blocks. Pass the layout as block_schema, not raw HTML "
"comments. When a schema is staged, share edit_url (not post_url) so the "
"user can approve."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/UploadMedia/Config.php:14
msgid "Upload Media"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/UploadMedia/Config.php:15
msgid ""
"Uploads an image (provide a public url, a local absolute file_path, or "
"base64_data) to the WordPress Media Library and returns its attachment id, "
"url, width and height. Images only ? cannot upload video or other file "
"types."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/SiteInfo/Config.php:14
msgid "Get Site Info"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/SiteInfo/Config.php:15
msgid "Returns WordPress site name, description, URL and version."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/PostTypes/Config.php:14
msgid "Get Post Types"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/PostTypes/Config.php:15
msgid ""
"Returns all registered WordPress post types with their label, public "
"visibility, and hierarchy."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/ManageTemplate/Config.php:14
msgid "Create or Edit Template"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/ManageTemplate/Config.php:15
msgid ""
"Creates, updates or deletes a Full Site Editing (FSE) template or template "
"part (set delete to remove); returns id, slug, edit_url and action. Pass "
"Blockish layouts as block_schema, never raw HTML. When a schema is staged, "
"share edit_url (not the preview link) so the user can approve."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/ManagePost/Config.php:14
msgid "Create or Edit Post"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/ManagePost/Config.php:15
msgid ""
"Creates a post (omit post_id) or edits one (provide post_id) of any "
"registered post type; returns post_id, post_url, edit_url and post_status. "
"Pass Blockish layouts as block_schema, never raw \"<!-- wp:... -->\" "
"markup. When a schema is staged, share edit_url (not post_url) so the user "
"can approve."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/ManageClass/Config.php:14
msgid "Create, Update or Delete CSS Class"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/ManageClass/Config.php:15
msgid ""
"Creates, updates or deletes a reusable Blockish Class Manager class (a "
"\"blockish-classes\" custom post) selected by the action param; returns "
"post_id, name, css_selector and content. You write only name and the JSON "
"style object (content) ? never raw CSS, and on update content fully "
"replaces the stored object (not merged). Only create a class for styling "
"that has no equivalent block attribute."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/GetTemplates/Config.php:14
msgid "Get Site Editor Templates"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/GetTemplates/Config.php:15
msgid ""
"Fetches existing Full Site Editing (FSE) templates (wp_template) and "
"template parts (wp_template_part) for the active theme, optionally filtered "
"by type."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/GetPosts/Config.php:14
msgid "Get Posts"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/GetPosts/Config.php:15
msgid ""
"Reads existing posts, pages or any registered post type, filterable by "
"post_type, search, status and pagination, or fetch one by post_id."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/GetMedia/Config.php:14
msgid "Get Media"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/GetMedia/Config.php:15
msgid ""
"Lists existing items in the WordPress Media Library, filterable by search, "
"mime_type and pagination."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/GetClasses/Config.php:14
msgid "Get CSS Classes"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/GetClasses/Config.php:15
msgid ""
"Returns all classes registered in the Blockish Class Manager, keyed by "
"name, each with its post_id, css_selector, parent_id, editable content and "
"compiled css. Call this before creating or updating classes to avoid "
"duplicates."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/GetClassManagerDocs/Config.php:14
msgid "Get Class Manager Docs"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/GetClassManagerDocs/Config.php:15
msgid ""
"Returns the full Blockish Class Manager reference ? how classes work, how "
"to write CSS, block attribute formats (classManager, "
"classManagerSubselector), parent vs child classes, responsive CSS, and "
"ready-to-use CSS patterns."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/ExtensionsInfo/Config.php:14
msgid "Get Extensions Info"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/ExtensionsInfo/Config.php:15
msgid "Returns total, active and inactive Blockish extension counts."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/BlocksInfo/Config.php:14
msgid "Get Blocks Info"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/BlocksInfo/Config.php:15
msgid ""
"Returns all Blockish blocks keyed by name, each with its status and an "
"optional \"parent\" key marking child/inner blocks."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/BlockDocs/Config.php:14
msgid "Get Block Docs"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Mcp/Abilities/BlockDocs/Config.php:15
msgid ""
"Returns the full Blockish block reference ? all blocks, their attributes, "
"formats (responsive object, typography, background, border, spacing, icon, "
"image) and markup examples."
msgstr ""